<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Saxifraga</i> <i>tolmiei</i> is characteristically present in the herbaceous and subshrub layers with <i>Carex</i> <i>helleri</i>, <i>Cystopteris</i> <i>fragilis</i>, <i>Luetkea</i> <i>pectinata</i>, <i>Luzula</i> <i>divaricata</i>, <i>Oxyria</i> <i>digyna</i> and <i>Senecio</i> <i>fremontii</i>. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 40 cm; cover is open. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> North-facing aspects where snow remains on the ground until late July or August. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Saxifraga tolmiei</i> as a FACU* plant. </div>
</div>

		
